        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-28 15:03:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nso, this \"left over information\" in tmti, who left it over and how come it was not wiped if it's not really needed anymore?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "01ae63d6fd35487390f30fc55369a845ef1c01c5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-03-28 16:22:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis llog steal process will walk through all of the config record client log, and convert each osc/mdc records into the osc/mdc records inside the MDT config,  and tmti will be used to collect the current mdc/osc information, which marked by \"add mdc\" marker pairs,  so once the end of the marker is reached, we need clear current tmti information, and be ready to collect next osc/mdc information,  otherwise, the leftover information from last osc/mdc will confuse the convertion process, for example mti_nids, etc.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "88ee0b52d5530ba4187f3d4da87743c009bef726",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-28 21:35:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, approved\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
